[3] China (Shandong)
Date: Mon 12 Oct 2020
Source: BBC News [edited]
https://www.bbc.com/news/world-asia-54504785


The Chinese city of Qingdao [Shandong province] is testing its entire population of 9 million people for COVID-19 over a period of 5 days. The mass testing comes after the discovery of a dozen cases linked to a hospital treating coronavirus patients arriving from abroad.

In May [2020], China tested the entire city of Wuhan -- home to 11 million people and the epicentre of the global pandemic. The country has largely brought the virus under control. That is in stark contrast to other parts of the world, where there are still high case numbers and lockdown restrictions of varying severity.

In a statement posted to Chinese social media site Weibo, Qingdao's Municipal Health Commission said 6 new cases and si6x asymptomatic cases had been discovered. All the cases were linked to the same hospital, said the state-run Global Times. The Chinese authorities now have a strategy of mass testing even when a new coronavirus cluster appears to be relatively minor, correspondents say.

The National Health Commission said on Monday [12 Oct 2020] that "the whole city will be tested within 5 days". Some 114 862 people -- including medical staff and newly hospitalised patients in the city's hospitals -- had already tested negative, Qingdao's health commission said.

Videos circulating online showed residents lining up late on Sunday [11 Oct 2020] to get tested, said the Global Times, adding that some of these test points were open from 07:00 to 23:00. The new cases come a week after China's Golden Week holiday -- which saw millions travel across the country. A Global Times report quoting the Qingdao Municipal Bureau of Culture and Tourism said the coastal city had received 4.47 million passenger trips over this period.

The nearby city of Jinan, in the same province as Qingdao, called for anyone who had visited the city since [23 Sep 2020] to get tested, according to a report by The Paper. Earlier last month [September 2020], Qingdao announced that 2 port workers who handled imported seafood had tested positive. They were not known to have infected anyone else.

Daily coronavirus infections have fallen drastically in China, and for the most part the country appears to have recovered from the worst. China currently has 91 305 virus cases and the death toll stands at 4746, according to WHO data. [This includes Hong Kong, Macau, and Taiwan].

China said 11 million people in the city [Wuhan] had been tested in 10 days earlier this year [2020]. Hundreds of testing centres were opened, with thousands of staff involved. They also mobilised teams to test disabled people, the elderly and those vulnerable in their own homes. One of the ways they sped up the process was to use batch- or pool-testing. In this process, a batch of between 5 and 10 samples was tested. Only if a sample tested positive would the team go back to carry out individual tests to see who was positive within the batch.

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

[This is the 4th occurrence of local transmission reported in China following the interruption of transmission from the 1st wave back in December [2019] through March 2020. In this instance, it appears as though imported cases may have been a nidus for a possible nosocomial outbreak although this information is suggested by the wording of the report but not confirmed as yet. While the cases were announced in Qingdao on 11 Oct 2020, the cases were not announced on the official reports from the National Health Commission until today, 12 Oct 2020. (http://www.nhc.gov.cn/xcs/yqtb/202010/400a3f95e1be4aa7b702ac45b96570f2.shtml)

Prior such events involved a Seafood Market enhanced outbreak in Beijing (363 cases); a market enhanced outbreak in Xinjiang Uygur autonomous region (832 cases), a seafood processing plant enhanced outbreak in Liaoning (100 cases). (See COVID-19 update (305): Spain seroprevalence, antigen test, WHO, global 20200707.7549897; COVID-19 update (347): Japan, countries, WHO, global 20200806.7651345; and COVID-19 update (361): tuberculosis, pandemics, selected countries, WHO, global 20200816.7683792).

We await further news on the epidemiology of this outbreak.

Qingdao is a major city in eastern Shandong province. A coastal city on the western shore of the Yellow Sea. According to Wikipedia, "Qingdao is a major nodal city on the 21st Century Maritime Silk Road arm of the Belt and Road Initiative that connects East Asia with Europe, and has the highest GDP of any city in the province." It is a major seaport with a naval base (https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Qingdao).

A map of China showing provinces can be seen at https://sacu.org/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/provmap.png and a HealthMap/ProMED-map is available at https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=7857069,155. - Mod.MPP]

