[The number of countries and territories reporting confirmed cases of COVID-19 to WHO remains at 216.

Data by country, area, or territory for 12 Oct 2020 can be accessed at https://promedmail.org/wp-content/uploads/world-pdf/WHO%20daily%20tablesOct12_1602534855.pdf.

- The Americas region reported 38.4% of daily case numbers and 46.3% of the daily deaths reported in the past 24 hours, maintaining its position as the most severely affected region, having reported more than 17.9 million cases. The USA and Brazil maintain their dominance, followed by Argentina, Colombia, Mexico, and Peru. Other countries reporting more than 1000 cases in the past 24 hours include Canada, Chile, and Costa Rica. Ecuador did not report any new cases in the past 24 hours.

- The European region reported 28.3% of daily case numbers and 15.3% of the daily deaths reported in the past 24 hours, and total cumulative cases reported exceed 7.0 million. Countries not reporting cases today (12 Oct 2020) include Spain, Germany, Israel, Kazakhstan, Sweden, Switzerland, Armenia, Norway, and Montenegro. France is dominant, followed by Russia, the UK, Czech Republic, Netherlands, Italy, Ukraine, Poland, and Romania. Other countries reporting more than 1000 cases in the past 24 hours include Hungary, Turkey, Austria, Portugal, and Slovakia.

- The Eastern Mediterranean region reported 5.9% of daily case numbers and 10.8% of the deaths reported in the past 24 hours, having reported a cumulative total of greater than 2.6 million cases. Iran is dominant, followed by Morocco, Iraq, Oman, Tunisia, UAE, Libya, and Lebanon. Jordan and Kuwait reported more than 500 cases but less than 1000.

- The African region reported 1.4% of daily case numbers and 3.2% of the deaths reported in the past 24 hours and has reported more than 1.2 million cases. South Africa is dominant, followed by Ethiopia, Kenya, Uganda, Nigeria, Cabo Verde, Mozambique, Algeria, and Angola.

- The Western Pacific region reported 1.2% of daily case numbers and 2.0% of the deaths reported in the past 24 hours, having reported a cumulative total of 0.65 million cases. As previously, the Philippines maintains its dominance, followed by Malaysia, Japan, and South Korea.

- The South East Asia region reported 24.9% of the daily newly reported cases and 22.3% of reported deaths in the past 24 hours, having reported a cumulative total of more than 7.9 million cases. As previously, India remains dominant, followed by Indonesia, Nepal, Myanmar, and Bangladesh.

On the Overview tab at the WHO source URL, the epidemic curve of confirmed COVID-19 cases by WHO region, 30 Dec 2019 through 12 Oct 2020 is an excellent visual representation of the pandemic. - Mod.MPP]

